  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "Combine the flour and butter in a bowl, mixing until it resembles coarse crumbs.",
    "Gradually add the heavy cream, stirring to form a dough.",
    "Wrap the dough around the clay pot, pressing the edges to seal.",
    "Prick the crust with a fork to allow steam to escape.",
    "In a separate bowl, mix the crushed tomatoes, minced garlic, grated parmesan, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Pour the tomato mixture into the clay pot.",
    "Place the clay pot in the preheated oven and bake for 30 minutes.",
    "Remove the pot from the oven and let it rest for 5 minutes.",
    "Serve the garlicky tomato gratin hot, garnished with chopped parsley."
  ],
